==English==

===Etymology===
From the ''[[Bible]]'' "Give not that which is holy unto the dogs, neither '''cast ye your pearls before swine''', lest they trample them under their feet, and turn again and rend you." - [[KJV]], [[s:Bible_(King_James)/Matthew#7:6|''Matthew 7:6'']]

===Phrase===
'''[[cast]] [[pearl]]s [[before]] [[swine]]'''

# {{idiom}} To give things of value to those who will not understand or appreciate it.

